<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFB2FFE8FCCCFB1B4A81F854" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB2FFE8FCCCFB1B4D9BFA75" blockId="3.[801,1452,1228,1957]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FCCCFB1B4AF8FB15" box="[839,922,1229,1252]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Notes. –</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB2FFE8FC29FB1A4DE0FB15" author="BURMAN" box="[930,1154,1228,1252]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" page="231" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768: 231)</bibRefCitation>
’s description was based on a 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FCBDFB3B4A14FAF5" box="[822,886,1261,1284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Pryon</emphasis>
collection from 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFB2FFE8FBBEFB3B4D07FAF5" box="[1077,1125,1261,1284]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Java</collectingRegion>
. Asingle 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FB52FB3B4C7BFAF5" box="[1241,1305,1261,1284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Pryon</emphasis>
collection is preserved in G-PREL [G00800023] (
<figureCitation id="49D32A11FFB2FFE8FB53FADA4C7DFAD5" box="[1240,1311,1292,1316]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[136,164,1914,1933]" captionTargetBox="[304,1306,276,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[304,1306,276,1863]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. – Original material of Blechnum indicum Burm. f., a Pryon collection from Java with the polynomial cited in the protologue representing Asplenium longissimum Blume in G-PREL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5684540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5684540/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). It bears in 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FCAAFAFB4A08FAB5" box="[801,874,1325,1348]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Pryon’s</emphasis>
handwriting the polynomial cited in the protologue (“ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FCB8FA9A4C0EFA95" box="[819,1388,1356,1380]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Filix lonchitidis facie alis denticulatis dupliciter auriculatis</emphasis>
”) and undoubtedly corresponds to the description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB2FFE8FCCCFA5A4D0DF974" blockId="3.[801,1452,1228,1957]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB2FFE8FCCCFA5A4DB5FA55" author="CHAMBERS &amp; FARRANT" box="[839,1239,1420,1444]" editor="ORCHARD, A. E. &amp; P. M. MCCARTHY MCCARTHY" firstAuthor="CHAMBERS" page="710" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" pagination="364 - 384" part="48" refId="ref9002" refString="CHAMBERS, T. C. &amp; P. A. FARRANT (1998 a). Blechnaceae, Blechnum. In: ORCHARD, A. E. &amp; P. M. MCCARTHY MCCARTHY (ed.), Fl. Australia 48: 364 - 384; 710 (appendix)." title="Blechnaceae, Blechnum" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Fl. Australia" year="1998" yearSuffix="a">CHAMBERS &amp; FARRANT (1998a: 710</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB2FFE8FB68FA5A4C29FA55" author="CHAMBERS &amp; FARRANT" box="[1251,1355,1420,1444]" firstAuthor="CHAMBERS" journalOrPublisher="Blumea" page="315" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" pagination="283 - 350" part="46" refId="ref9107" refString="CHAMBERS, T. C. &amp; P. A. FARRANT (2001). Revision of Blechnum in Malesia. Blumea 46: 283 - 350." title="Revision of Blechnum in Malesia" type="journal article" year="2001">2001: 315</bibRefCitation>
) erroneously stated that the type was lost and replaced by the extant 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FCAAFA1B4A02FA15" box="[801,864,1485,1508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Pryon</emphasis>
specimen mentioned above, which would not match the description of the species and thus the plants currently known as 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB2FFE8FC19F9DA4D36F9D5" box="[914,1108,1548,1572]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Blechnaceae" genus="Blechnum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="indicum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FC19F9DA4D36F9D5" box="[914,1108,1548,1572]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Blechnum indicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the widespread 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB2FFE8FAB6F9DA4A9EF9B5" authority="Blume" authorityName="Blume" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longissimum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FAB6F9DA4ACAF9B5" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Asplenium longissimum</emphasis>
Blume
</taxonomicName>
published in 1828 (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB2FFE8FB6CF9FB4C1DF9B5" author="BLUME" box="[1255,1407,1580,1604]" firstAuthor="BLUME" journalOrPublisher="Leiden" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" refId="ref8775" refString="BLUME, C. L. (1828). Enumeratio plantarum Javae et insularum adjacentium. Leiden." title="Enumeratio plantarum Javae et insularum adjacentium" type="book" year="1828">BLUME, 1828</bibRefCitation>
), as correctly determined by F. Ballard (on 
<date id="A5561054FFB2FFE8FB46F99A4C07F995" box="[1229,1381,1612,1636]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" value="1951-09-10">Sept. 10, 1951</date>
). They designated therefore a 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFB2FFE8FB98F9BB4D09F974" box="[1043,1131,1645,1669]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">neotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB2FFE8FCCCF95A4A81F854" blockId="3.[801,1452,1228,1957]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">
As the 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FC16F95B4ABCF955" box="[925,990,1677,1700]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Pryon</emphasis>
specimen clearly represents the type of Burman’s name, making it the oldest available name for 
<taxonomicName id="16E84D17FFB2FFE8FA1FF97B4AFCF915" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longissimum">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB2FFE8FA1FF97B4AFCF915" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">A. longissimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Chambers &amp; Farrant’s neotypification cannot be accepted. In order to enable the further use of both names and to preserve nomenclatural stability (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB2FFE8FB12F8DA4C1AF8D5" author="TURLAND" box="[1177,1400,1804,1828]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="TURLAND" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" refId="ref10318" refString="TURLAND, N. J., J. H. WIERSEMA, F. R. BARRIE, W. GREUTER, D. L. HAWKSWORTH, P. S. HERENDEEN, S. KNAPP, W. - H. KUSBER, D. - Z. LI, K. MARHOLD, T. W. MAY, J. MCNEILL, A. M. MONRO, J. PRADO, M. J. PRICE &amp; G. F. SMITH (2018). International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Veg. 159." title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017" type="proceedings" year="2018">TURLAND et al., 2018</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 14.2), a proposal to conserve Burman’s name with a conserved type is needed (MAZUMDAR et al., in prep.). The gathering selected by Chambers &amp; Ferrant as 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFB2FFE8FB2CF8BB4D9FF874" box="[1191,1277,1901,1925]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">neotype</typeStatus>
will be retained as conserved type.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
